This paper is about deep learning deployment on embedded systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their training and inference. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as image recognition is mentioned as one of the application domains where deep learning has been successful. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.EM (Emerging Technologies), as embedded systems are a rapidly growing area of technology.
